{{See|KAON}}
==English==
===Etymology===
From contracted pronunciation of ''K-[[meson]]''
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''kaon'''
#{{particles}} any of four [[unstable]] [[subatomic particle]]s, [[meson]]s, they are a [[combination]] of a [[strange]] [[quark]] or [[antiquark]] and either an [[up]] or [[down]] quark or antiquark
#* K<sup>0</sup> - strange quark + down antiquark
#* K<sup>0*</sup> (its antiparticle) - down quark + strange antiquark
#* K<sup>+</sup> - strange quark + up antiquark
#* K<sup>-</sup> (its antiparticle) - up quark + strange antiquark